2) [u]The Debate: To Spend or to Save?[/u] 

As the global economic recovery continues, we explore the battle between economists, politicians and countries on whether to spend money on stimulus, or pay down debt to avoid further economic hardship.

[u]Guests:[/u]

[b]Josh Bivens[/b] is an economist with the Economic Policy Institute, and author of Everybody Wins Except for Most of Us: What Economics Teaches About Globalization.

[b]Mark Blyth[/b] is a Professor of International Political Economy in the Political Science Department, and a Faculty Fellow at the Watson Institute for International Studies, at Brown University.

[b]Chris Edwards[/b] is the Director of Tax Policy Studies at the Cato Institute. He is the author of Downsizing the Federal Government and co-author of Global Tax Revolution.

[b]David Laidler[/b] is Fellow in Residence at the C.D. Howe Institute, and Professor Emeritus at the University of Western Ontario.

